:R-HSA-174437  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0032201 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Two endonucleases, Dna2 and flap endonuclease 1 (FEN-1), are responsible for resolving the nascent flap structure (Tsurimoto and Stillman 1991). The Dna2 endonuclease/helicase in yeast is a monomer of approximately 172 kDa. Human FEN-1 is a single polypeptide of approximately 42 kDa. Replication Protein A regulates the switching of endonucleases during the removal of the displaced flap (Tsurimoto et al.1991)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Removal of the Flap Intermediate from the C-strand" ;
        dc:contributor      "Reviewed: Price, C, 2006-07-13 18:33:38" , "Authored: Blackburn, EH, Seidel, J, 2006-03-09 19:41:08" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Hayashi, Makoto T, 2020-04-29" , "Edited: Orlic-Milacic, Marija, 2020-05-04" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
